import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="region", y="population", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Region', ylabel='Population')
    ax.axhline(y=data['population'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Population')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="rate", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axhline(y=data['rate'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean rate')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Average Rate')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average rate of each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['region', 'color']]
    data = data.groupby(['region', 'color']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    colors = ['#ff9999','#66b3ff','#99ff99','#ffcc99']
    ax.pie(data['counts'], labels=data['region'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=colors)
    ax.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of colors across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    g = sns.FacetGrid(data, col="region", col_wrap=3, height=4, aspect=1.5)
    g.map(sns.histplot, "rate", color="steelblue", bins=10)
    g.set_titles("{col_name}")
    g.fig.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)
    g.fig.suptitle("What is the distribution of rate across different regions?")
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
